license for the export of any item from the five categories listed below to sensitive end-users in the terrorist-supporting countries.
Pursuant to Section 6(j) of the Act, BXA requires a license for the export of the following items to military or other sensitive end-users in designated terrorist-supporting countries: 1) All items subject to national security controls, except computers with a performance level of less than 500 million theoretical operations per second (Wassenaar Arrangement)1.
All items subject to chemical and biological weapons proliferation controls (Australia Group).
All dual-use items subject to missile-proliferation controls (Missile Technology Control Regime).
All items subject to nuclear weapons-proliferation controls (Nuclear Referral List).
All military-related items (items controlled by CCL entries ending with the number 18).
