In FY 2001, BXA approved seven license applications valued at $1,187,232 for North Korea; no applications were rejected and one (valued at $11,067) was RWA'd.
On September 17, 1999, President Clinton announced his decision to ease some of the maintained against North Korea.
The sanctions easing was implemented in June 2000, most U.S. consumer goods being authorized for export to North Korea.
